title.narrative: 601 SOCIAL PROTECTION PROGRAMMES FOR CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS AND THEIR FAMILIES

description.narrative: National, UNICEF programming state governments and other partners have adequate capacity to plan, integrate, implement and monitor social protection programmes for children, adolescents and their families especially addressing marginalized and vulnerable at most critical stages of life cycle and vulnerable situations (*urban slums, climate change impacts, insurgencies) by 2022, which contributes to Access To Justice, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children (Covid), Evaluation And Research, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Social policies and strategies inform more effective and efficient planning, budgeting and implementation of social service programmes for reducing inequities and gender inequalities especially for the most vulnerable and marginalized children and adolescents by 2022
